3. CURRENT USE CASES & WORKFLOWS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

UC-1  LOG A SERVICE
  1. User enters 6-digit customer ID on home page (or pastes from clipboard)
  2. Clicks "Go" → navigates to customer page
  3. Clicks "Log Service" → POST service record → table refreshes
  4. Progress bar updates (e.g., "4 of 10")

UC-2  VIEW CUSTOMER HISTORY
  1. User navigates to #customer/{id} (via Go or Paste+Go)
  2. All services for that customer are fetched and displayed newest-first
  3. Redeemed services show the redemption date; redeemer rows show ★ FREE

UC-3  REDEEM FREE SERVICE
  1. Customer page loads → unredeemed count ≥ 10
  2. Redeem button appears (pulsing animation)
  3. User clicks "Redeem free Oil Change"
  4. Oldest 10 unredeemed services are PATCHed:
     - All 10 get the same redemption_id timestamp
     - The 10th (newest of batch) gets redeemer = true
  5. Table refreshes, progress resets for remaining unredeemed

UC-4  AUTO-REDIRECT HOME
  1. Customer page sets localStorage deadline = now + 2 min
  2. Countdown displays in fixed corner
  3. On expiry (or tab re-focus after expiry) → navigate to #home

UC-5  BULK DELETE (Admin)
  1. Click "Database Control" → overlay step 1
  2. Click "Delete all logged services" → step 2 confirmation
  3. Type DELETEALL → submits → DELETEs all service records
  4. Success card with close button → navigates home


4. NEW DATA MODEL — SUPABASE TABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

TABLE: logged_services
  Column        | Type      | Notes
  ───────────── | ───────── | ───────────────────────────────────────────
  id            | uuid      | PK, default gen_random_uuid()
  number        | text      | Format "LSXXXXXXX" (LS + 7-char unique)
                |           | Generated client-side at creation
  customer_id   | text      | 6-digit string, NOT NULL
  created_on    | timestamptz | default now(), service timestamp
  redemption    | text      | NULL = unredeemed; references
                |           | loyalty_redemptions.number when redeemed

TABLE: loyalty_redemptions
  Column        | Type      | Notes
  ───────────── | ───────── | ───────────────────────────────────────────
  id            | uuid      | PK, default gen_random_uuid()
  number        | text      | Format "REDXXXXXXX" (RED + 7-char unique)
  created_on    | timestamptz | default now(), redemption timestamp
  triggered_by  | text      | References logged_services.number (the
                |           | 10th service that triggered redemption)

RELATIONSHIPS:
  logged_services.redemption → loyalty_redemptions.number (many-to-one)
  loyalty_redemptions.triggered_by → logged_services.number (one-to-one)

MAPPING FROM OLD MODEL:
  Old service record        →  logged_services row
  Old redemption_id (group) →  loyalty_redemptions row
  Old redeemer = true row   →  The service whose .number is stored in
                               loyalty_redemptions.triggered_by


5. MIGRATION MAPPING — OLD FIELDS TO NEW
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  OLD FIELD        →  NEW LOCATION
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  service_id       →  logged_services.created_on
  customer_id      →  logged_services.customer_id (unchanged)
  redemption_id    →  logged_services.redemption (now stores
                      loyalty_redemptions.number instead of timestamp)
  redeemer         →  REMOVED from logged_services; derived from
                      loyalty_redemptions.triggered_by matching
                      logged_services.number
  id               →  logged_services.id (now uuid)


