7. IMPLEMENTATION PLAN — STEP BY STEP
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 1: Supabase Client (src/config/supabase.js)
  - Import supabase-js from CDN (esm.sh)
  - Export createClient with placeholder URL + anon key
  - Single shared client instance

STEP 2: Auth Service (src/services/auth.js)
  - signIn(email, password) → supabase.auth.signInWithPassword
  - signOut() → supabase.auth.signOut
  - getSession() → supabase.auth.getSession
  - onAuthStateChange(callback) → supabase.auth.onAuthStateChange
  - All return consistent { data, error } shape

STEP 3: Data Services
  src/services/loggedServices.js:
    - generateNumber() → "LS" + 7 random alphanumeric chars
    - create(customerId) → insert into logged_services
    - getByCustomer(customerId) → select where customer_id, order desc
    - getUnredeemedByCustomer(customerId) → where redemption IS NULL, asc
    - markRedeemed(ids, redemptionNumber) → update redemption column
    - deleteAll() → delete from logged_services (admin)

  src/services/loyaltyRedemptions.js:
    - generateNumber() → "RED" + 7 random alphanumeric chars
    - create(triggeredByNumber) → insert into loyalty_redemptions
    - getByRedemptionNumber(number) → select by number

STEP 4: Config API Rewrite (src/config/api.js)
  - REMOVE old fetch wrapper
  - EXPORT data service functions as unified interface
  - Feature code calls api.logService(), api.getServices(), etc.
  - Under the hood, calls Supabase services

STEP 5: Login Feature (src/features/login/)
  - login.js: renders email + password form, calls auth.signIn
  - login.css: centered card matching app theme
  - On success: triggers route to #home
  - On failure: inline error message

STEP 6: Auth Gate (src/app.js)
  - On DOMContentLoaded: check session
  - If no session → render login page, block hash routing
  - If session exists → proceed with normal routing
  - onAuthStateChange: re-evaluate gate on sign-in / sign-out
  - Add logout button to app header (visible when authenticated)

STEP 7: Customer Feature Update (src/features/customer/customer.js)
  - Replace api() calls with data service calls
  - Redemption flow:
    1. Fetch unredeemed services (redemption IS NULL)
    2. Take oldest 10
    3. The 10th service's .number is the trigger
    4. Create loyalty_redemption row (triggered_by = 10th.number)
    5. Update all 10 services: set redemption = new redemption.number
    6. Refresh table
  - Table display:
    - "Service Date" → logged_services.created_on
    - "Redeemed" → if redemption is set, show date from joined
      loyalty_redemptions.created_on (or just "Yes"/"—")
    - "★ FREE" badge → if this service.number matches any
      loyalty_redemptions.triggered_by

STEP 8: Home Feature Update (src/features/home/home.js)
  - Replace api() POST call with loggedServices.create()
  - No other functional changes needed

STEP 9: Database Control Update (src/app.js)
  - Replace per-record DELETE loop with loggedServices.deleteAll()
  - Also delete all loyalty_redemptions in same flow

STEP 10: index.html Updates
  - Add login.css stylesheet link
  - Add Supabase JS CDN script (or rely on ESM import)


8. NUMBER GENERATION SCHEMES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Service number:    "LS" + 7 chars  → e.g. "LS3kF9m2x"
  Redemption number: "RED" + 7 chars → e.g. "REDaB7q1Yz"

  Generation: crypto.randomUUID().slice(0,7) or similar
  Collision risk: negligible for this scale


9. SUPABASE FOLLOW-UP STEPS (POST-DEPLOY)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
After the Supabase project is created, these are the ONLY steps needed:

  □ 1. Create Supabase project at supabase.com
  □ 2. Run table creation SQL (provided in src/config/supabase.js comments)
  □ 3. Set Row Level Security policies:
        - logged_services: authenticated users can SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE
        - loyalty_redemptions: authenticated users can SELECT, INSERT
  □ 4. Create a user account in Supabase Auth dashboard
  □ 5. Replace placeholders in src/config/supabase.js:
        - SUPABASE_URL → your project URL
        - SUPABASE_ANON_KEY → your anon/public key
  □ 6. Remove json-server dependency (optional, can keep for dev)

  That's it. The app is live.


10. SQL FOR TABLE CREATION (Reference)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  CREATE TABLE logged_services (
    id          uuid DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() PRIMARY KEY,
    number      text NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    customer_id text NOT NULL,
    created_on  timestamptz DEFAULT now() NOT NULL,
    redemption  text  -- NULL = unredeemed; holds loyalty_redemptions.number
  );

  CREATE TABLE loyalty_redemptions (
    id           uuid DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() PRIMARY KEY,
    number       text NOT NULL UNIQUE,
    created_on   timestamptz DEFAULT now() NOT NULL,
    triggered_by text NOT NULL  -- logged_services.number of the 10th service
  );

  -- Indexes
  CREATE INDEX idx_ls_customer ON logged_services(customer_id);
  CREATE INDEX idx_ls_redemption ON logged_services(redemption);
  CREATE INDEX idx_lr_triggered ON loyalty_redemptions(triggered_by);

  -- RLS (apply after enabling RLS on both tables)
  ALTER TABLE logged_services ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
  ALTER TABLE loyalty_redemptions ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

  CREATE POLICY "Authenticated full access" ON logged_services
    FOR ALL USING (auth.role() = 'authenticated');

  CREATE POLICY "Authenticated full access" ON loyalty_redemptions
    FOR ALL USING (auth.role() = 'authenticated');
